It is vendored as a read-only reference implementation. **We do not hold rights
to it and cannot license it to anyone.** Two separate reasons:

1. The upstream repository contains no licence file. Under the Berne Convention
   the default is all rights reserved, so there is no grant to pass on — not
   even for the code.

2. Its art and audio are derivative works of the Touhou Project by Team Shanghai
   Alice (ZUN), whose rights are held by neither us nor upstream.

Nothing under `toho-like-js/` may be redistributed as part of this project, and
no asset from it may appear in a build. Everything we ship is original work:
placeholder art and sound are generated procedurally at runtime, specifically so
that no borrowed asset is ever needed. See CLAUDE.md rule 7 and docs/assets.md.

If this project is ever published, `toho-like-js/` should be removed from the
distributed tree, and from history if the repository itself is published.


